This paper deals with Markov Decision Processes, which are a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence and machine learning. The use of Value and Policy Iteration, as well as the development of variations of these algorithms, suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI and cs.LG. The focus on optimization and the use of error bounds also suggest that the paper could be categorized under cs.DS. The mention of stationary and non-stationary policies, as well as the use of discount factors, suggest that the paper could be categorized under cs.SY. Finally, the use of mathematical analysis and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.MA.
